Description: Fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear shows a very small flat area, next to it two wide impressions of a string with a width of 0.3 cm. The front side is flat, running down towards the edges and shows an impression of an oval scarab-like seal with the lower part preserved. Visible is a circumferential line, there seemed to have been two columns of which the left is preserved with remains of a nb-sign above an n, underneath HqA-wAs.t and a third vertical sign, on top of a standing line.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
